reviews.review_text: Great (and still downloadable) show This could be the best sounding Rubin & Cherise by the band I've heard on Archive thus far.  Keep up the good work guys!

Thank you! Great show! great AUD recording. I would like to thank all the people that helped get this show here and to the tapers that taped it. Thank you! i have been waiting a long time to find a recording of this that was not a SBD and now i have! You made my day!
Lively recording of a great 91 show Thanks to the tapers and everyone involved in making this one available. I'd love to hear a matrix!!

@radler http://www.archive.org/details/gd1991-03-17.senn-ME80.wklitz.94062.flac16


my personal favorite of all time... the HUGE echo of happiness.

My First Show Well as all of us know it was spectacular.The first show seems to resonate the longest, the first experience...the hundreds of thousands of, well people...and the afternoon sunlight....the way the day smelled...ol factory in full swing. We may as well have been there once upon a time, long ago and once again.... Hmmm aside from that I remember camping across the road from the venue...it was gen admin so you could literally walk right up to the front of the stage if you wanted to, which of course I never did.But we had a great vantage point stage left on that little hill with the fence at the top.... I think there were bathrooms(blue lagoons) up there as well.
Anyway I remember a very big rainbow of balloons that came down from the crowd onto stage.....very momentus....also i remember the mix being weird, you couldnt hear bobbys guitar  or bruces vox....sorry im digressing...peesh
Smiling Thanks for sharing this show. I was there and remember the sweet days of summer and the Grateful Dead! Happy.

First Show Wow - I just found this- this was my first show- and it blew my mind. How I was just transported back to my first show. That is a sweet gift that I can't repay. Thank you- The recording is great.

Buckeye Lake '91 Super chill vibe, a vast space, I was 21, my second show.   We got dosed, The Violent Femmes opened.  The band played Rueben and Cherise...it was magical.  Jerry was still in fine form.  The Playin' Jam is awesome.  Thank you for a stellar audience recording.
